body: Re-release of 0.36.

* Don't try to extract webcal link during authentication
* Increase target SDK version to 28 in compliance with Play Store rules

* Make event and birthday sync work again
* Updated translations

* Fixed authentication through web.facebook.com
* Increased timeouts when downloading data
* Don't leak unstripped URL with user tokens to logs
* Workaround a crash when updating lastSync option
* Improved German translation
* Improved Privacy Policy

* More authentication fixes
* "Report bug" action now automatically attaches sync longs
* Updated Kotlin
* Updated translations

* Proper fix for Facebook authentication
* Fixed card layout with multiple accounts on the main activity

* Fixed authentication with Facebook
* Updated translations
* Updated to Kotlin 1.3.11

* Update Facebook calendar endpoints
* Fix handling or errors during key extraction

* Fixed login after recent Facebook changes
* Added links to app's Facebook page
* Minor bugfixes
* Updated translations
Workaround invalid all-day event reminder where there should be none
* Fix updating the app through Play Store

* Fix event duplication on sync (#45)
* Fix auto sync not working for new users (#44)
* Fix enable calendar slider in settings being inaccessible (#42)
* final release promoted from 0.26 (beta 1) to fix versioning for F-Droid

name: 0.26 (beta 2)
body:
* Fixed all-day events being duplicated (#41)
* Added German localization

name: 0.26 (beta 1)
body:
* Fixed sync not working for new users or users whose login has expired
* Complete UI redesign
* Custom reminders for all-day events (#25)
* Support for multiple accounts (#27)
* Automatic handling of expired authentication (#28)
* Fixed calendar preferences not being applied (#32)
* Updated translations
* Fix login to accounts with two-factor authentication enabled

name: v0.24
body:
* Fix crash when loading local events
* Fix crash when parsing token URL during authentication
* Stop the authentication process when the activity is closed
* Update to Kotlin 1.2.30
* fix crashes

* Fix typo in string (issue #23)
* Make the link to Facebook in event description optional (issue #24)
* Updated translations
* Duch translation (thanks, Heimen)
* Fix all events being deleted when the app fails to download the iCal file
* Minor visual and layout improvements on the main screen
* Refactoring and code cleanup
* Port the app from Java to Kotlin
* Better logging and exception handling
* Fix icon and title of the main activity
* Fix iCal link extraction

name: v0.21
body:
* Add Polish translation (thanks to Lukasz)
* Add 36-hour reminder
* Remove birthday events of unfriended friends

name: v0.19
body: * Hotfix for broken authentication in previous release. Lesson learned, don't watch TV while programming and test your changes...

name: v0.18
body:
* Birthday events now include link to user's profile page
* Added 'Sync Now' button to the main activity (requires READ_SYNC_STATS permission)
* Fixed toolbar in Settings view
* Better handling of some error cases
* Reduced the size of logfile
* Using newer User-Agent when loading Facebook pages
* Better logging when retrieving iCal link fails
* Norwegian translation (thanks to Allan Nordhøy)

name: v0.17
body: * Fix Czech localization

name: v0.16
body:
* fix crash when calendar is enabled during sync
* use custom notification to ask for re-authentication
* prevent duplicate events
* fix event availability based on the calendar
* opt-out from Android WebView anonymous telemetrics
* code clean-up

name: v0.15
body: * Try to address issues with events not syncing - the app will ask users to re-authenticate.

name: v0.14
body:
* added option to choose custom language for birthdays and events
* Czech localization
* fixed duplicated events and birthdays (hopefully)
* fixed changing calendar colors
* fixed default values for reminders not showing
* various crash fixes

name: v0.13
body:
* fix crashes on update/delete
* fix duplicate events issue
* fix support for KitKat and older
* lots of minor code improvements

name: v0.12
body:
* new feature to configure color for each calendar
* new feature to completely disable certain calendars
* improved sync scheduling
* fix various crashes introduced in the previous release
* fix usage of new API on older Android versions
* fix duplicated birthday events (issue #8)
* fix the updating of existing events
* fix birthdays and events language not following device language (issue #11)

name: v0.11
body:
* Make events sync again
* Make events from private groups sync again
* Drop support for Android  4.1 and older
